texts.text: v0.1.1 alpha was the first version of Pocket Edition released for all Android devices.[1]

1 Additions
2 Internal Version
3 Demo
4 J-version
5 J-version Demo
6 References

Auto-Jump.
Version exclusive: Adds touchscreen controls.
New UI for touch screen devices.
The internal version of v0.1.1 alpha is 0.1.1(1015) and has a size of 1.56 MB.

A free "lite" demo of v0.1.1 alpha was released on Google Play on an unknown release date. In mid-2014, it was removed from the Play/App stores. The internal version is the same as the official release.

v0.1.1j alpha was released on Google Play on an unknown release date, providing support for older Android devices.[2] This J-version has differing sounds from the non J-version, this is especially prevalent when walking on grass. This version also has a lack of sounds for the title and world selection screens.

A free J-version "lite" demo of v0.1.1 alpha was released on Google Play on an unknown release date. In mid-2014, it was removed from the Play/App stores. The internal version is the same as the j-version.
"Minecraft: Pocket Edition Update Information Thread" (dead link) – Minecraft Forum.
